The paper deals with the expressibility of data vectors as linear combinations of others, which is a problem in discrete mathematics and combinatorics. The use of integer linear constraints suggests a connection to linear programming and optimization, which falls under cs.DM. The study of reversible data vectors and their relationship to finitely generated subgroups suggests a connection to group theory, which falls under cs.GR. The application of these concepts to counter machines and Coloured Petri nets suggests a connection to formal languages and automata theory, which falls under cs.LO. The use of unordered data vectors suggests a connection to set theory and combinatorics, which falls under cs.CC. Finally, the study of data vectors as finitely supported functions suggests a connection to programming languages and semantics, which falls under cs.PL.
